    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Pani Puri is a beloved Indian street food consisting of crispy puris filled with spicy tangy water, potatoes, chickpeas, and tamarind chutney.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>30 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>20 puris (store-bought or homemade)</li>
        <li>2 boiled potatoes (mashed)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup boiled chickpeas</li>
        <li>1/4 cup chopped onions</li>
        <li>Mint-coriander water (pani)</li>
        <li>Tamarind chutney</li>
        <li>Black salt, cumin powder, chaat masala to taste</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Mix mashed potatoes, chickpeas, onions, and spices for the filling.</li>
        <li>Crack open the puris from the top.</li>
        <li>Add the filling and drizzle with tamarind chutney.</li>
        <li>Pour the chilled mint-coriander pani into each puri.</li>
        <li>Serve immediately and enjoy the burst of flavors!</li>
    </ol>
